The paper deals with nonadaptive group testing, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of Bernoulli tests and the analysis of their capacity is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also involves typicality bounds and algorithms, which are topics in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of the optimality of nonadaptive group testing strategies involves combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
